<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-06-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-06-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="61" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d61">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-06-16"><hi rend="italic">June 16,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay states that the United States embassy in Russia telegraphs that
                            the Russian minister for foreign affairs requests that Mr. Conger <pb facs="0149" n="65" xml:id="pg_65"/> communicate to the Russian
                            minister at Peking the demands of the United States relative to
                            localities to be opened to trade. He promises that the minister of
                            Russia will be authorized to frankly state to the Chinese Government the
                            attitude of Russia.</p>
                        <p>Mr. Conger is instructed to confer fully with the Russian minister and
                            report the result to the Department.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>